title: For Sale:  FN Five Seven 5.7 w/ AMMO  Military/LEO pistol (Double-Action Only (DAO))
postcontent: FN Five Seven 5.7 Double-Action Only (DAO) pistol, Imported year 2000. The FN Five-seven DAO pistols were the best!!! The first variant Five-seven DAO pistol was originally restricted by FN to law enforcement and military customers then. It is double-action only with a trigger pull of 4.5 to 6.5 daN (10 to 14 lbf) . It has a pebbled grip pattern, smoothly-contoured accessory rail, low profile fixed sights and a circular-shaped trigger guard designed to improve gloved use. It does not have a slide release and the slide is not serrated as on newer variants, but a portion of the slide is instead slightly concave to aid grasping. The original Five-seven pistols were shipped with only two (2) 20 round magazines. These mags will NOT work in later Five-seven IOM or USG variant unless the magazine safety has been removed or deactivated. This pistol comes in the original FNH hard case with operator’s instructions/manual, cleaning kit, and (2) 20 round magazines. PLUS ~ 500 rounds SS198LF LEO/

title: For Sale:  PWS MK-1 AR-15
postcontent:
PRIMARY WEAPON SYSTEMS (PWS) 5.56 X 45 

14.5 PINNED BARREL (Establishes 16" legal length)

The MK1 series, developed by Primary Weapons Systems, is a significant product improvement for the M4/M16-type carbines and rifles. Utilizing our proven long stroke piston system, the MK1 series greatly reduces fouling in the action of the weapon making it as reliable as the AK47 that it was designed after.

The MK1 series has been used in Iraq and Afghanistan, and has gained wide popularity with security personnel, law enforcement and civilians alike.

The origins of the MK1 series began with the fascination in the simplicity and reliability of the AK47 combined with a deep-rooted appreciation for the ergonomics of the M4/M16 platform. Having a significant understanding of the deficiencies in the direct gas impingement operating system found on conventional M4/M16-style weapons, PWS developed the MK1 series with the professional in mind.

Significant improvements have been made over both the direct gas impingement operating system and previous offerings of piston-driven operating systems. The product improvements made by PWS have addressed reliability and performance issues as well as reduced carrier tilt, cam pin wear and carrier bounce. In addition, we have one of the lightest systems on the market today!

An innovative hand guard system utilizes a proprietary non-free float system that allows the end user or unit armorer to replace individual rails as needed without removing the barrel, barrel nut or even other rails. This system allows the user to attach numerous Picatinny rail-mounted devices such as sights, lights, and laser aiming devices.

The PWS proprietary operating system utilizes an operating rod that is attached to the carrier and a floating head piston that is attached to the operating rod. The MK1 series is built to be a true combat carbine. With no unnecessary gas adjustments and only one moving assembly, this is the most rugged, simple and versatile piston operating system available.

The MK1 series is available as a complete rifle or as a complete upper receiver for use on existing M4/M16 style lower receivers.

Weight: 6 lbs, 15 oz

Overall length: 32.9"

Barrel length: 16.1"

title: For Sale:  M1 Garand - serious shooter
postcontent:
For sale - an M1 Garand as returned to blueprint specs!

You know that our President recently halted the import of M1 Garands and has substantially reduced the supply of these rifles. 

The CMP Garands are usually okay, but how many of them are in the same condition as originally issued?

I love shooting this rifle.  The first time I shouldered it, I slung it up and blasted a clay pigeon laying on the ground at 120 meters, offhand.  

That said, I am trying to consolidate major calibers, so I am keeping the 308's and selling this rifle.

The rifle is tight.  Clean. In excellent shape.  

It is a shooter.  You could pay Fulton Armory a lot more and get one this nice.

The stock has a couple dings, but the mechanicals are superb, perfect function.  Patton was right, this is an amazing implement of war.

I'm selling it for $1100 and this is more than fair.  

I also have a fair bit of 30-06 ammo I am willing to discuss with the buyer of this rifle, a little over 1200 rds, some of it loose in ammo cans, some of it in en bloc clips, all 1200+ rounds military surplus M2 ball.  I'm not selling the ammo separately at this time.
